        request-id) is wired at the composition root (or a dedicated boundary wiring module) and documented.
      - >-
        TBP Gate (TBP-FASTAPI-01/G-FASTAPI-COMPOSITION-ROOT-WIRING): When the resolved schema strategy is
        code_bootstrap, the composition root invokes its plane-owned schema bootstrap entrypoint before serving traffic
        instead of leaving schema creation dormant.
      - >-
        TBP Gate (TBP-FASTAPI-01/G-FASTAPI-COMPOSITION-ROOT-WIRING): Fail-closed auth/policy exceptions are mapped to
        explicit HTTP responses at the composition root (or a dedicated boundary wiring module) rather than surfacing as
        raw framework 500s.
      - >-
        TBP Gate (TBP-FASTAPI-01/G-FASTAPI-FRAMEWORK-MANAGED-DEPENDENCY-PROVIDERS): When framework-managed dependency
        wiring is selected, route modules consume services/providers via a TBP-declared dependency provider boundary
        rather than constructing them inline.
      - >-
        TBP Gate (TBP-FASTAPI-01/G-FASTAPI-FRAMEWORK-MANAGED-DEPENDENCY-PROVIDERS): The dependency provider boundary
        stays within FastAPI-owned boundary code and does not introduce a second bespoke DI/container subsystem.
      - >-
        Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-AP-TENANT-CARRIER-01-auth_claim): Tenant context from a verified auth
        claim inside the Authorization credential (for example a JWT `tenant_id` claim), not from client-supplied tenant
        headers.
      - >-
        Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-CPAP-TENANT-CARRIER-01-auth_claim): Tenant context from a verified
        auth claim inside the Authorization credential (for example a JWT `tenant_id` claim), not from client-supplied
        tenant headers.
      - >-
